  Scenario: Successfully retrieve a pet by valid existing ID

    Given the user wants to get the information for a pet
    When the user sends a valid request with an existing id
    Then the user gets the id, category, name, photoUrls, tags and status

  Scenario: Retrieve a pet with a non-existing ID

    Given the user wants to get the information for a pet
    When the user sends a valid request with a non existing id
    Then the user gets "Pet not found" error message

Scenario: Retrieve a pet with an invalid ID format

    Given the user wants to get the information for a pet
    When the user sends a valid request with a invalid id
    Then the user gets a 404 error message

Scenario: Successfully retrieve pets with status "available"
   Given the user wants to find pets by status
   When the user sends a valid request with the status "available"
   Then the user gets a list of pets with status "available"

  Scenario: Successfully retrieve pets with status "sold"
    Given the user wants to find pets by status
    When the user sends a valid request with the status "sold"
    Then the user gets a list of pets with status "sold"

  Scenario: Successfully retrieve pets with status "pending"
    Given the user wants to find pets by status
    When the user sends a valid request with the status "pending"
    Then the user gets a list of pets with status "pending"

  Scenario: Retrieve pets with an invalid status value
    Given the user wants to find pets by status
    When the user sends a valid request with an invalid status "unknown"
    Then the user gets an empty list of pets
    And the response status code should be 200

  Scenario: Retrieve pets without providing a status value
    Given the user wants to find pets by status
    When the user sends a request without specifying a status
    Then the user gets an empty list of pets
    And the response status code should be 200

  Scenario: Successfully add a new pet with all valid details
    Given the user wants to add a new pet to the store
    When the user sends a POST request to "/pet" with all the fields
    Then the response status code should be 200
    And the response body should contain the pet details
    And newly generated id


  Scenario: Add a new pet with an empty body
    Given the user wants to add a new pet to the store
    When the user sends a POST request to "/pet" with an empty body
    Then the response status code should be 200
    And the response body should contain the pet details with a newly generated id
    And empty photoUrls list and empty tag list


  Scenario: Add a new pet with missing name in tags object
    Given the user wants to add a new pet to the store
    When the user sends a POST request to "/pet" with missing name in tags object
    Then the response status code should be 200
    And the response body should contain the pet details with a tag object without name field
    And newly generated id

  Scenario: Add a new pet with missing id in tags object
    Given the user wants to add a new pet to the store
    When the user sends a POST request to "/pet" with missing id in tags object
    Then the response status code should be 200
    And the response body should contain the pet details
    And newly generated id
    And the id in tags object is the default one -- 0

  Scenario: Add a new pet with missing id in category object
    Given the user wants to add a new pet to the store
    When the user sends a POST request to "/pet" with missing id in category object
    Then the response status code should be 200
    And the response body should contain the pet details
    And newly generated id
    And the id in category object is the default one -- 0


  Scenario: Add a new pet with missing name in category object
    Given the user wants to add a new pet to the store
    When the user sends a POST request to "/pet" with missing name in category object
    Then the response status code should be 200
    And the response body should contain the pet details with a category object without name field
    And newly generated id


  Scenario: Upload an image with missing additional data
    Given the user wants to uploads an image
    When the user sends a POST request to "/pet" with an existing petId
    And missing additionalMetadata and file to upload
    The response should be 200 Ok
    and the body response

    {
      "code": 0,
      "type": "string",
      "message": "string"
    }


  Scenario: Upload an image with all required fields additional data
    Given the user wants to uploads an image
    When the user sends a POST request to "/pet" with all required fields
    The response should be 200 Ok
    and the body response

    {
      "code": 0,
      "type": "string",
      "message": "string"
    }

  Scenario: Upload an image with all the fields

    Given the user wants to uploads an image
    When the user sends a POST request to "/pet" all the fields
    The response should be 200 Ok
    and the body response

    {
      "code": 0,
      "type": "string",
      "message": "string"
    }

  Scenario: Upload an image with a non existing petId
    Given the user wants to uploads an image
    When the user sends a POST request to "/pet" with a non existing petId
    The response should be 200 Ok
    and the body response
    {
      "code": 0,
      "type": "string",
      "message": "string"
    }

   Scenario: Upload an image with an invalid petId
    Given the user wants to uploads an image
    When the user sends a POST request to "/pet" with an invalid petId
    The response should be 404 Not found

Feature: Update an existing pet


  Scenario: Successfully update a pet with all valid details
    Given the user wants to update an existing pet
    When the user sends a PUT request to "/pet" with the following details
      | id                | category.id | category.name | name   | photoUrls | tags.id | tags.name | status    |
      | 8966745555555555555 | 0           | string        | doggie | string    | 0       | string    | available |
    Then the response status code should be 200
    And the response body should contain the pet details
    And the pet details should include the id, category, name, photoUrls, tags, and status

  Scenario: Update pet with a non-existent ID
    Given the user wants to update a pet with a non-existent ID
    When the user sends a PUT request to "/pet" with the following details
      | id                | category.id | category.name | name   | photoUrls | tags.id | tags.name | status    |
      | 9999999999999999999 | 0           | string        | doggie | string    | 0       | string    | available |
    Then the response status code should be 404
    And the response body should contain an error message indicating that the pet was not found

  Scenario: Update pet with a missing required field
    Given the user wants to update a pet but with a missing required field
    When the user sends a PUT request to "/pet" with the following details
      | id                | category.id | category.name | photoUrls | tags.id | tags.name | status    |
      | 8966745555555555555 | 0           | string        | string    | 0       | string    | available |
    Then the response status code should be 400
    And the response body should contain an error message indicating that the "name" field is required

  Scenario: Update pet with an invalid ID
    Given the user wants to update a pet with an invalid ID
    When the user sends a PUT request to "/pet" with the following details
      | id         | category.id | category.name | name   | photoUrls | tags.id | tags.name | status    |
      | invalid_id | 0           | string        | doggie | string    | 0       | string    | available |
    Then the response status code should be 400
    And the response body should contain an error message indicating that the ID is invalid

  Scenario: Update pet with an invalid status value
    Given the user wants to update a pet with an invalid status value
    When the user sends a PUT request to "/pet" with the following details
      | id                | category.id | category.name | name   | photoUrls | tags.id | tags.name | status        |
      | 8966745555555555555 | 0           | string        | doggie | string    | 0       | string    | invalid_status |
    Then the response status code should be 400
    And the response body should contain an error message indicating that the status value is invalid

  Scenario: Update pet with empty photoUrls and tags
    Given the user wants to update a pet with empty photoUrls and tags
    When the user sends a PUT request to "/pet" with the following details
      | id                | category.id | category.name | name   | photoUrls | tags | status    |
      | 8966745555555555555 | 0           | string        | doggie | []        | []   | available |
    Then the response status code should be 200
    And the response body should contain the pet details with empty photoUrls and tags arrays
    And the response body should include a valid id

  Scenario: Update pet with missing category name
    Given the user wants to update a pet with a missing category name
    When the user sends a PUT request to "/pet" with the following details
      | id                | category.id | name   | photoUrls | tags.id | tags.name | status    |
      | 8966745555555555555 | 0           | doggie | string    | 0       | string    | available |
    Then the response status code should be 200
    And the response body should contain the pet details with the category object missing the name field
    And the response body should include a valid id

Feature: Update pet information using form data


  Scenario: Successfully update pet with valid form data
    Given the user wants to update the pet with ID 131439890
    When the user sends a POST request to "/pet/131439890" with the following form-encoded data
      | field   | value      |
      | name    | test       |
      | status  | available  |
    Then the response status code should be 200
    And the response body should contain the updated pet details
    And the pet details should include the id, name, and status

  Scenario: Update pet with missing required field
    Given the user wants to update the pet with ID 131439890 but with a missing required field
    When the user sends a POST request to "/pet/131439890" with the following form data
      | field   | value      |
      | status  | available  |
    Then the response status code should be 400
    And the response body should contain an error message indicating that the "name" field is required

  Scenario: Update pet with invalid status value
    Given the user wants to update the pet with ID 131439890 but with an invalid status value
    When the user sends a POST request to "/pet/131439890" with the following form data
      | field   | value         |
      | name    | test          |
      | status  | invalid_status |
    Then the response status code should be 400
    And the response body should contain an error message indicating that the status value is invalid

  Scenario: Update pet with invalid ID format
    Given the user wants to update the pet with an invalid ID format
    When the user sends a POST request to "/pet/invalid_id" with the following form data
      | field   | value      |
      | name    | test       |
      | status  | available  |
    Then the response status code should be 404
    And the response body should contain an error message indicating that the pet was not found

  Scenario: Update pet with empty form data
    Given the user wants to update the pet with ID 131439890 but sends empty form-encoded data
    When the user sends a POST request to "/pet/131439890" with empty form-encoded data
    Then the response status code should be 400
    And the response body should contain an error message indicating that no data was provided

Feature: Delete an existing pet

  Scenario: Successfully delete an existing pet
    Given the user wants to delete the pet with ID 143
    When the user sends a DELETE request to "/pet/143"
    Then the response status code should be 200
    And the response body should contain a confirmation message indicating successful deletion

  Scenario: Delete a non-existent pet
    Given the user wants to delete a pet with a non-existent ID
    When the user sends a DELETE request to "/pet/999999999"
    Then the response status code should be 404
    And the response body should contain an error message indicating that the pet was not found

  Scenario: Delete a pet with invalid ID format
    Given the user wants to delete a pet with an invalid ID format
    When the user sends a DELETE request to "/pet/invalid_id"
    Then the response status code should be 400
    And the response body should contain an error message indicating that the ID format is invalid

  Scenario: Delete a pet with no ID
    Given the user wants to delete a pet but does not provide an ID
    When the user sends a DELETE request to "/pet/"
    Then the response status code should be 404
    And the response body should contain an error message indicating that no pet ID was provided

  Scenario: Delete a pet with a valid ID but the server is down
    Given the user wants to delete a pet with ID 143 but the server is down
    When the user sends a DELETE request to "/pet/143"
    Then the response status code should be 500
    And the response body should contain an error message indicating that the server is unavailable











